  • Method Details

    • createProperty

      public Property createProperty(Double propertyPrice, Double propertyArea, Address propertyAddress, Double propertyDistanceToCentre, List<Photograph> propertyPhotographs, PropertyType propertyType, Store store, Client client, DateTime date)
      Sends the parameters to the PropertyRepository object to create a new Apartment object with those specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      propertyPrice - the Land's price.
      propertyArea - the Land's area.
      propertyAddress - the Land's address.
      propertyDistanceToCentre - the Land's distance to the city centre.
      propertyPhotographs - the Land's list of photographs.
      propertyType - the type of the Property, should always be 'Land' in this case
      store - the Store where the Land will be listed.
      client - the Client that registered the Land.
      date - the date that the Land was registered in the system.
      Returns:
      a Land object.

    • createProperty

      public Property createProperty(Double propertyPrice, Double propertyArea, Address propertyAddress, Double propertyDistanceToCentre, List<Photograph> propertyPhotographs, Integer propertyBedroomNumber, Integer propertyBathroomNumber, Integer propertyParkingSpaceNumber, List<String> propertyEquipmentList, PropertyType propertyType, Store store, Client client, DateTime date)
      Sends the parameters to the PropertyRepository object to create a new Apartment object with those specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      propertyPrice - the Apartment's price.
      propertyArea - the Apartment's area.
      propertyAddress - the Apartment's address.
      propertyDistanceToCentre - the Apartment's distance to the city centre.
      propertyPhotographs - the Apartment's list of photographs.
      propertyBedroomNumber - the number of bedrooms in the Apartment.
      propertyBathroomNumber - the number of bathrooms in the Apartment.
      propertyParkingSpaceNumber - the number of parking spaces in the Apartment.
      propertyEquipmentList - the Apartment's list of available equipment.
      propertyType - the type of the Property, should always be 'Apartment' in this case
      store - the Store where the Apartment will be listed.
      client - the Client that registered the Apartment.
      date - the date that the Land was registered in the system.
      Returns:
      a Apartment object.

    • createProperty

      public Property createProperty(Double propertyPrice, Double propertyArea, Address propertyAddress, Double propertyDistanceToCentre, List<Photograph> propertyPhotographs, Integer propertyBedroomNumber, Integer propertyBathroomNumber, Integer propertyParkingSpaceNumber, List<String> propertyEquipmentList, Boolean propertyHasBasement, Boolean propertyHasLoft, String propertySunExposure, PropertyType propertyType, Store store, Client client, DateTime date)
      Sends the parameters to the PropertyRepository object to create a new House object with those specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      propertyPrice - the House's price.
      propertyArea - the House's area.
      propertyAddress - the House's address.
      propertyDistanceToCentre - the House's distance to the city centre.
      propertyPhotographs - the House's list of photographs.
      propertyBedroomNumber - the number of bedrooms in the House.
      propertyBathroomNumber - the number of bathrooms in the House.
      propertyParkingSpaceNumber - the number of parking spaces in the House.
      propertyEquipmentList - the House's list of available equipment.
      propertyHasBasement - if the House has a basement.
      propertyHasLoft - if the House has a loft.
      propertySunExposure - the sun exposure of the house.
      propertyType - the type of the Property, should always be 'House' in this case
      store - the Store where the House will be listed.
      client - the Client that registered the House.
      date - the date that the Land was registered in the system.
      Returns:
      a House object.

    • createAnnouncementRequest

      public AnnouncementRequest createAnnouncementRequest(Integer rentDuration, BusinessType businessType, Property property, Agent agent, Client client)
      Sends the parameters to the Store object to create a new announcement request for a given rent duration, business type, property, agent, and client.
      Parameters:
      rentDuration - the duration of the rent in months
      businessType - the type of business associated with the announcement request
      property - the property associated with the announcement request
      agent - the agent associated with the announcement request
      client - the client associated with the announcement request
      Returns:
      the created announcement request if it was successfully added to the announcement request repository, null otherwise
